#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:2
msgid "pytest-2.7.1: bug fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:4
msgid ""
"pytest is a mature Python testing tool with more than 1100 tests against "
"itself, passing on many different interpreters and platforms. This release "
"is supposed to be drop-in compatible to 2.7.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:8
msgid "See below for the changes and see docs at:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:10
msgid "http://pytest.org"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:12
msgid "As usual, you can upgrade from pypi via::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:14
msgid "pip install -U pytest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:16
msgid "Thanks to all who contributed to this release, among them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:18
msgid "Bruno Oliveira Holger Krekel Ionel Maries Cristian Floris Bruynooghe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:23
msgid "Happy testing, The py.test Development Team"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:28
msgid "2.7.1 (compared to 2.7.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:30
msgid ""
"fix issue731: do not get confused by the braces which may be present and "
"unbalanced in an object's repr while collapsing False explanations.  Thanks "
"Carl Meyer for the report and test case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:34
msgid ""
"fix issue553: properly handling inspect.getsourcelines failures in "
"FixtureLookupError which would lead to an internal error, obfuscating the "
"original problem. Thanks talljosh for initial diagnose/patch and Bruno "
"Oliveira for final patch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:39
msgid ""
"fix issue660: properly report scope-mismatch-access errors independently "
"from ordering of fixture arguments.  Also avoid the pytest internal "
"traceback which does not provide information to the user. Thanks Holger "
"Krekel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:44
msgid ""
"streamlined and documented release process.  Also all versions (in setup.py "
"and documentation generation) are now read from _pytest/__init__.py. Thanks "
"Holger Krekel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:48
msgid ""
"fixed docs to remove the notion that yield-fixtures are experimental. They "
"are here to stay :)  Thanks Bruno Oliveira."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:51
msgid ""
"Support building wheels by using environment markers for the requirements.  "
"Thanks Ionel Maries Cristian."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:54
msgid ""
"fixed regression to 2.6.4 which surfaced e.g. in lost stdout capture "
"printing when tests raised SystemExit. Thanks Holger Krekel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.7.1.rst:57
msgid ""
"reintroduced _pytest fixture of the pytester plugin which is used at least "
"by pytest-xdist."
msgstr ""
